\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid9308090 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you tell me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Alice Emma Gannon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 3 Comyns Close, Canning Town, E.16.4JJ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you tell me the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 1915. October the thirty-first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 29th of August 1897.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Cundy Road, Custom House. Custom House, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well we moved to a - another house in - which is now Jersey Road but was called Jennet Road and - that - time in our lives we could move out of
 one house into another because there was plenty of accommodation available. And we didn't live there very long because it was an upstairs flat and my mother was handicapped so we moved to a downstairs flat in a road called Hooper Road. Where it's almost 
entirely demolished now and being rebuilt. That's in Custom House too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How long did you stay at Hooper Road for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I think about three years we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And then where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well we - we moved to Garvey Road, a little house - small house at Garvey Road. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you stay there long?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
I don't - about two years I would think, about two years, and then we moved to Tidal Basin and - the flat was too small and we moved back to Garvey Road to a - three bedroomed hou
se and my mother died in that house. We were there 'til 1912. 1912 when my mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You were there for quite a long time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I suppose about four years really. 'Cos I - I wasn't quite fifteen when my mother died, so - it would have been about that time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did you go after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
We went back to Tidal Basin and I lived there 'til I was married and I was married at eighteen and went and lived with my mother at - my husband's mother and - my first daughter was born in that h
ouse and we lived - I lived there 'til the end of the war and - that was at Crediton Road, yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you remember generally why your family moved from house to house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well in most case it was a question of - of - either more accommodation o
r less rent you see in those days, I mean a shilling on the rent made a lot of difference. I mean today it wouldn't would it, not a shilling, but in those days, when one was paying about four or five shillings for a house or a flat you could get one for a
 shilling cheaper you see it made a lot of - great deal of difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And there were plenty available?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes, plenty of accommodation, yes. Well the point was this, that so many people were so poor that they would pack into one room that - you'd get two or three families probably living in one house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I haven't got any brothers and - I had brothers, I don't know how many but they died but - I had five sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you tell me what order they came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well my eldest brother, he was - oh - I suppose he'd have been about eighty-four if he'd have been alive now. And then I had a sister who was two years younger than him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you remember what year she was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 She'd have bee
n eighty-one - eighty-two this year so - ohow far back is that. About - about '87 she would have been born wouldn't she, somewhere - 1887 or '88. '88, yes. '88. And the other sister was born in - '89. And I was born - there was another sister in between u
s
, I don't know - I think she would have been about eighteen months older than me so she would have been born in 1895, see, so - I was born in 1897, and then my mother had a boy eighteen months after me, so that would have made that about 1899 wouldn't it.
 
And I had another sister was born in - 1900. She's still alive. My two eldest sisters are both dead now, they died within the last four years. And - sister Emily was born in 1900 and - my mother did have twins after that, I couldn't tell you what year the
y were born in, oh about 1903 I think, and they both died. And then I had another sister born in 1906 and another - my younger sister was born in 1908. They are both - three younger sisters alive, and I am.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the two boys die shortly after birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
One died shortly after - well, he was nine months old. And the girl that died was about seven months old. But the eldest boy was two and a half. He had measles and pneumonia and he died. But I - wasn't born when he was there so I wouldn't know about hi
m at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh - he was fifty-three when he died and I was eighteen, take eighteen away from fifty-three, that's about - quick reckoning - thirty - thirty-five, yes, yes. Mother would have been thirty. Thirty, yes, when I was born, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He was born in Stepney. But his grandparents were born in Wales. He was Welsh by - sort of - parentage but he was born in Stepney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well he was a plumber. And incidentally music hall - he was on the music hall as well, he was a fine singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 As a job or just a spare time hobby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well as jobs, you know, as - sort of part time job really I suppose. His - as a matter of fact he - he knew Dan leno, he dance
d with Dan Leno and - Lottie Collins, you know, all that crowd, he knew all of those. I used to hear him talk about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So he did plumbing during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, and the music hall in the evening time, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he have any other jobs before or after that that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well he - I don't - I don't - don't - don't remember, he was an apprentice plumber and - he worked for the P }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9785491 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  O Company for years. He used to sometimes go abroad to India for them and Malta.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he work on boats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. On the boats and sort of go abroad to work for - the company up there. Oh he was away from home at times yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He did this music hall part time in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he ever stop plumbing and concentrate on music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No I don't think so. He may have done probably in his real younger days before I was born, I don't now anything about that of course, he used to talk about it so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And he continued with plumbing until he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Until he died, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
He was never out of work but he suffered - he had a great deal of - well - rheumatism - rheumatic gout they called it and probably that's where I get my arthritis from more than anything. He did suffer a
 great deal from that. And in the - the latter years of - I suppose the last two years of his life he seemed to get quite a lot of bronchitis. Whether, of course those days they didn't bother quite so much about it as they did today. Not only that, there 
wasn't the National Health business that - people were just had ill and had to look after themselves mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well she was born in Stepney. But her mother - her mother was a Kentish woman, my grandmother was, came 
from Kent. As a matter of fact she was married at Sevenoaks church. I don't know where my grandfather came from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Your mother was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8925657\charrsid16671506 brought up in K}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ent and then moved into Stepney?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I - I expect that's what happened, I don't know where my grandf
ather met her at all, but they were a Kentish family, all her brothers and sisters lived in Kent. They were a big Army family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Had your mother any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well her own mother had a tailoring - works and my mother - worked a
t home you see, my mother was first class tailoress. But she had a stroke at twenty-four, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8925657\charrsid16671506 hemorrhage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
 of the brain and of course - couldn't continue working. She never went to school, my mother didn't. She was the eldest and sort of looked after the family while her mother - while her mother was running the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So after twenty-four she could never work again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not to go out to work, she worked on her own home, she - after she recovered 1 - of course that was before I was born and - after she 
began to recover she started to do all her own work and washing. Though she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8925657\charrsid16671506 paralyzed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  all down one side, severely }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8925657\charrsid16671506 paralyzed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
. But she did her own - she got about quite well. Of course there were some things she couldn't do, I mean she couldn't climb on 
a chair or anything like that, but she would clean and - it was amazing how she would sort of hold the flannel and wring it and - the same with washing you know, she used to do her washing, the washing was beautiful too and her home was spotlessly clean.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But she could never go out to work again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Had she been able to do you think your father would have let her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I don't think he would have done while his health was good. Probably would have allowed her to if - if - yo
u know, she'd have been able to. But - he didn't like the idea of a woman working. Of course the old type of man didn't. A woman's place was in the home really and that was it. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Id'd like to ask you about life at home when you were a child, up until you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well I don't know, we had - we didn't have very much money, we didn't have anything very much of this worlds goods but we had a happy life. We made our own enjoyment. We used to - cut things out and make furniture out of matc
hboxes and chestnuts and the shells of walnuts and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Which house can you remember best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where my mother died, yes. Garvey Road, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How many rooms were there in that house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 There was four rooms in the house, two up and two do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12669757\charrsid16671506 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 n and a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8925657\charrsid16671506 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
itchenette. Kitchenette. You didn't call it a kitchenette them days, you called it the wash house. Funny how - you know, names alter as you grow older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you cook in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, we did the cooking. Well I say, 
yes, we never had a gas stove, we cooked by fire. And my father - didn't like gas stoves, he didn't like gas cooking, he always said he could taste the gas, but I don't believe it, but he said he could. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well I never had any brothers then, there was just my two younger sisters, my mother and father and myself. Once my mother let one room to a young couple and - were in difficulties and she let the room to them fo
r a little while until they got theirselves out of difficulty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You said she did her own washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. But you see - from a very young child and - we were all trained to do something in the 
home. I mean my first job was to clean the knives, forks and spoons, used to have a - what we called a knife board and - most children in those days in poorer families were taught you know, taught to do things in the home. As I say I used to have - my fir
s
t job was the knife board and I used to have to clean knives, forks and spoons with brick dust and - and then wash them after, and if they wasn't clean I had to do them again. The prongs of the forks were all examined, you know, to see that they were all 
clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How often did you have to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Every Saturday morning that was my job. This - you know - it sounds awful today doesn't it to tell a child of six years of age but - it didn't come hard really. Not at the time - and I got a ha'penny at t
he end of the day. So that - well it was our weekly money, a ha'penny. If somebody came along and gave us a penny we thought we were rich. 'Course one would get much more for a ha'penny those days you couldn't get anything today could you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And all of you had your set jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes, we all had set jobs. And my mother had - a meat dish cover, they were metal, and when I got a little bit older I had to clean them and - there was tins on the mantelshelf for tea and that sort of thing and I had to clea
n them. Little things came along as I got older. Then - then you had to start, I suppose about eight years of age, started washing up and - between seven and eight - washing up and wiping. And then my mother started teaching me how to clean the floors, sh
e would - tell me, you know, I wasn't to take a too big a pace and - rinse it and wring the flannel out in the water and dry it well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 She really taught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, she taught us, yes. And - she was thorough in her - in teaching us you know, it was
n't just slapdash. Corners had to be gone into and if the corner wasn't done well you done it again. And the edge of the lino was picked up to see that you wiped the dust from underneath, that sort of thing. And then I started cleaning windows. I could si
t out of a window upstairs when I was nine years of age and clean the windows outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You fell out did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, didn't fell out. Sit out - clean the windows upstairs. Kids today - be terrified if they saw a kid sit out of a window. I used to
 do it. I was about nine years - nine, ten years old - used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You were probably very capable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes. Well my - I was eight years old when my mother had my sister May and - mother was doing something one day and I got the water and started bathing the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How long did you have to continue doing your tasks, after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh well of course mother died before I was fifteen and I had to take over the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you just kept on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, yes. Kept on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have to do anything to help your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have any tasks to help him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Only - no, no, only just that, work in the house you know. He was a very capable man himself in the house. He could do anything in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he help your mother with any of the jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He did clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, he'd clean windows and all that sort of thing and then get down and scrub the floor if it was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How about washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh he'd wash up, yes. But of course as we got older we had to do that of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about laying fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He - not much in the way of decoration, I don't - people didn't used to do so much decoration those days. But - he'd light t
he fire of a morning before he went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he do these things regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. Oh no, he'd do them in the morning before he went out, light the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he ever dress or undress or bath the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Never. No. Was very part
icular about that. He could come in of an evening time and go into the - as I say into the back kitchen - 'course there was no bathroom - and he'd shut the back kitchen doors and strip to the waist and have a good wash. But none of us - were allowed to go
 out there while he was washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And he didn't ever bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, he did and he used to read to my mother a great deal because she can't read and he was a - he - he was a - a very g
ood reader and he would read for her quite a lot. And I learnt to read very quickly, I could sit and read books, if he wasn't there I would take up and from where he'd left off and read to my mother. I was very - I - I learnt to read very quickly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, he used take - used to take us up to - into a football ground and you know walks and that sort of thing. But he didn't go out a great deal without my mother. Not a great deal. He used to go to concerts some
times there might be - generally an actor of - what they called a benefit concert in those days, if a man had been I'll a long time or out of work or met with an accident, they would get what they called a benefit concert up, and probably father would be 
doing a turn, of course mother and I would go when he was going. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would your father look after you if your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. She did - very seldom went out though on her own, very seldom that he did look after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother or your father make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well my mother had been a dress - my mother could have made anything but owing to her affliction - but she did used to cut the things out and I used to have to sit and sew them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You actually did the sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father do any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, he would do some sewing, he'd put buttons on and all that sort of thing. He was quite - quite handy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother or father or both mend anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Your father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were your clothes new or secondhand generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Mostly - well I - I would say in our latter - as I got up - a - a bigger child they were second hand, as a younger child they were new because my father was earning g
ood money at that time. But of course as his health broke there was no money coming in, once anyone was ill or out of work there was nothing coming in. But my mother's mother was very good in making us things and sending down. She herself was a very good 
dressmaker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If things were bought where were they bought from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well in the local shops mostly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Any special time of the year were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Christmastime mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about shoes, did your father or mother make or mend your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 My father always mended our shoes leather, but my grandfather, who was a bootmaker, used to make our - mend our boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you generally have new boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He made them so your mother and father never had to buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When did you have new ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh they used to last a long time, about once a year I suppose. 'Cos they were - they were all le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12669757\charrsid16671506 ather in those days and they did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  last and father used to mend them of course. And then when grandfat
her got - when he gave up his business there used to be a shop in - Custom House where they used to make boots of all - all leather. You could get a pair of boots those days from two and eleven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12669757\charrsid16671506  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 pence. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And they made them to order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And they made them, yes, yes, measured them. A good pair of boots would cost perhaps four and eleven, five and eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the older children have to help the younger children with things that they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Dressing them for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes. They would do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the younger children have to do anything for the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I don't - well of course not in our home they didn't. My two youngest sisters were too young really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
This is rather funny, my mother used to keep me up, whether it was cor company I don't know but the younger ones went to bed but I used to be kept up. I didn't go to bed, not so very early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you go to bed with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, before she went to bed but - normally I suppose about nine o'clock, half past nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 This was when your father was out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes. When he was in I used to go to bed early. But if he had to be out I was kept up, I suppose more for company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What time would the younger ones go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - about seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother or anyone else put you and them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well my mother used to put me to bed when I was smaller and my eldest sister w
ho was seven years older than me, but when the younger ones came along they hadn't - they wasn't at home then and I used to put the younger ones to bed. Help mother wash them and put them to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - about eight years old I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I never shared the bed - I was the lucky one, I always had a bed to my - to myself, but I shared the bedroom with the sisters. Yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your parents have the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 They had the other bedroom, yes. Normally the young - if there was a baby they slept in the same bedroom - parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What room did you have your bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Used to have it in the living room or in the kitchen as we called it in those days in front of the fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Downstairs you had the little kitchenette?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
We had a - a sort of kitchenette and then the - which you called the back kitchen or the wash house, and then we had the kitchen which was today we call the living room, 
see, and the bedrooms. So that we used to have a big zinc washing bath in you know and bath in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But there were two rooms downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What was the other room downstairs called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well you'd either have it for a parlour if you had enough room or have it for a bedroom whichever the case may be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you have it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well we had it for a parlour in the first place and then of course when there was other children came along it was used as a bedroom.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh about twice a week. But we were washed - sort of washed down every night before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh only once a week in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 In the living room, the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You said your mother cooked on an open fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was that a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, that was a range, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well before we went to school of a morning or - you know when - about eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What members of the family were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh, just mum and - kiddies and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would your father have already gone to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, he would have already gone to work, he used to go out at seven o'clock. He never ate breakfast before he went out, perhaps a piece of bread and butter with a cup tea. Take mother up a cup of tea and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you all usually eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Quaker Qats mostly we used to have for our breakfast. Sunday morning of course - we'd get an egg or rasher of bacon or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about at midday, what did you call that meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 That was called our dinner, we never called it lunch, it was dinner, yes, dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father come home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, he never had dinner at home, always had dinner at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother sit down with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What sort of things might you have to eat or drink for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well, whatever was going like stew perhaps one day and perhaps chops, liver and bacon, perhaps a meat pudding or meat pie - if we were lucky and the money was there. And - I suppose almost the same as people have today. Chickens of cou
rse were a luxury, you only got a chicken of a Christmas. That was a luxury really. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What was the evening meal called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well just tea. And we used to have - we were a family that liked fish, you know, fish was very cheap so that was either
 a bloater or haddock or something like that for tea. Bread and butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your father there then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes, father was there for tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No. Cake - make their own cakes. Yes, yes, make cakes and pastries and bread pudding or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Mother never made jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Mother used to make pickles, yes. She used to - make piccalilli, mustard pickle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, we never made wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Or medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well of course - mother used to send for stuff from the chemist to make up medicines, I think most people did those days you know. For coughs and that sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, we didn't have a garden big enough for that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, we used to have fruit, f
ather always used to buy fruit at the end of the week when he came home from work he'd stop - as he came along and go in and buy fruit for us and - sweets, you know, so that - on a Sunday morning we always had our sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Wasn't any about them days as I know of. Not - not tinned fruit - not tinned vegetables or fruit really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you keep any livestock at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 We had rabbits one time for a little while but - I don't think mother was too fond of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were they pets or to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well that was it, if you kept them as pet you didn't like eating them so - and - so that's why we didn't have them really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So she looked after them when you had them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I used to yes, but - I wasn't too keen. Never have been too keen on keeping - animals of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I suppose about four times a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever eat tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. This was the only tinned meat that I knew of was coned meat and my father wouldn't have it in the house. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Some people got extra meat such as rabbit from poaching, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, you couldn't do any poaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Many times. So did I too when my children was little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. He was a very - he was a very fair man in that way, we had to sit down at the table together and we had to share. He would never have
 more than my - if there wasn't sufficient for my mother he wouldn't have his. And rather funnily my husband was the same disposition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No. He was very strict on that point, no talking at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You have a bit of everything, if you didn't eat it - well you had to eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What was your parents attitude if you left something uneaten on your plage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You sat there 'til you ate it. That was my father's attitude, mother was a little bit lenient but not far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask for it to be passed or did you have to wait '
til it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, if you just asked for it to bed passed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh if there was enough there you could have a second helping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Definitely no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not until father had finished and then you had to say grace and please may I leave the table.
 And if father said you sit there 'til I'm ready you sat there 'til he - 'til he was ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And you always sat down to the table for your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, we did rather funnily. And this even happened after my mother died, my mother place was left.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How was the meal served and who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well father - if you - if it meant cutting meat father had to cut the meat because mother couldn't. And as I got older I would help dish the 
vegetables out. So that we all sat down together. And this went through the whole of my married life too with my children. Although I had a big family we all sat down at the table together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well near enough all the
 same practically, you know, by the time you - sort of the meat was cut and put on the plates the vegetables so that we all sat down together you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your father given his first or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, he' probably - practically he'd almost sit down last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh well I don't remember much about this, I suppose - they would have sat in their pram, they had a small pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would they have been fed first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes, mother would - when they got a little older and they could sit in the - there was a high chair, sit alongside of mother at the table. But then gain when I got older you see, I - you see I was old enough - with my two younger sisters to sit and - h
elp them feed them, I would cut their food up and sit and help feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How old were you when your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Nearly fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you remember if she was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, she was. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was she motherly did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. More so than I've ever done, my mother - she - showed a great deal of affection, I've always been more of a - I don't know, we sort of - we were very close family but we don't show it. You see my girl walked in today and - t
a-ra, I'm off and this is - this - that -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But your mother was the sort who would put her arm round you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes. Yes, she would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I think she shared her worries with me whe
n it came to it. You see, I mean - I was at home, the other two were married and - I was at home, in fact one younger than - the eldest one lived with my grandmother for years 'til she married, and the next eldest went - when she was fifteen she went into
 service which left me at home and - I - I was sort of - mother's companion and - and mother shared her troubles with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she have a lot of difficulties because of the fact that she was paralysed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 She never - she never seemed to show it, she never talked about it. She never said, well - she never made any fuss about it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have any adolescent problems that you might have talked to your mother about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I don't think I had time to think about them really because mother died 
as I say at fifteen I was left with the two younger children to bring up and I never had any time to worry about any - any adolescent problems. Father died three years after and the kiddies was left, this was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your father an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, he was rather. Yes, he made - he made quite a - a great deal of fuss of us kids you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. I - I - I missed him terribly when he died because he used to sit and explain such a lot to me. If I
 was reading something and I didn't understand it and - I always remember him - something about the - splitting the atom when I was a child and - this used to baffle me and I said to him one day, dad, what do they mean by splitting the atom? He said, the 
day they learn to split the atom my girl, he said, is the day that one's got to think of the end of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506  the world. And how s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
ure he was. And I still didn't - couldn't understand what it meant by splitting the atom. But these were the sort of things I could sit -
 politics, you know. There was a terrific big strike on in 1912, the year my mother died, and people were starving, literally starving, and - he - and - and I couldn't understand why this was. And - and he explained to me why this was brought about - beca
use -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 After your mother died was he a help to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. He'd come home and help, you know, the children - help me get them to bed and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But you said he was strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, he was very strict. He was a very strict man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 As far as behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well we had to be very obedient, this was, you know, this was - and we couldn't speak until we were spoken to, I mean, it was an att
itude of - children should be seen and not heard in those days. And if anybody came in and you - you happened to - I mean, children are free and easy today - and you happened to walk in and say - quiet - and you had to be quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they bring you up to behave towards your sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well - to be - sort of - motherly towards them as far as I can see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If you were playing with another child and that child hit you how were you expected to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not to go in crying to mother or father, just - either took it or hit them back. That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You were expected to be independent like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you think they considered certain things important in life or were they ambitious for their children in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well father was ambitious, he hoped that - you know - I would have passed the scholarship and gone on to something higher, but of course - rather fu
nnily the very week I was going to sit the scholarship I was taken ill, and whether it was nerves or what it was I don't know but I was ill. So of course I never sat for it. But he wanted me to go to evening classes but of course mother dying, that - was 
the end of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So he was ambitious in a wor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 dly sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. He was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they feel that certain things in life were right or wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I don't think they thought so much about it those days, I think they wanted to bring us
 up to be respectable decent citizens and - father - I - I remember the very first school report I ever took home and it was during my childhood that school reports came out, and I - I know the very first school report I took home I came fifth n the class
 and he was so proud of it, in fact he carried it about in his pocket for a long time I think. It was something wonderful you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was he particularly attached to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I think he was. Yes, think he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Never heard a swear word in our house. No. My never mother swore in her life. What father done outside I don't know. But he never swore in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did any of you children swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And when grown ups were talking you weren't allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no. No. Wouldn't have to join in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well you was punished in some way - probably - might get a smack but if you didn't get a smack you was punis
hed in some other way - probably - deprived of something or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 More father than mother. Mother was very lenient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But sometimes by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I don't never remember my mother sort of - she - she'd tell us - she'd say she
 was going to tell father when he came home and - but she never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. I was eight years old. Went up the Beckton Road, used to go paddling up there in the - what we called the 
swamps, in the ditches, and I lost a brand new pair of boots, another girl stole them. And when I got home I got a - got a good smack bottom for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 From your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. And - my mother stopped him but - anyway I happened to know where the k
id lived and mother and somebody else went round and got these boots back. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, I do. I was terribly indignant 'cos it wasn't my fault I thought, in my mind, that I'd lost the boots. But
 - suppose it wasn't really, I'd pout them beside of me and this girl pinched them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you didn't feel too happy about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. And another time I went out on a Sunday with dire threats, I'd got a pretty little dress on with forget-me-nots on a
nd a big straw hat tied round with ribbon, I was about eight years old, dire threats not to get a mark on me frock because I was going to auntie's to tea. And I met up with a little boy wh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 
o lived next door and he was a Roman Catholic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  and I was Church of En
gland, so he said, don't go to Sunday school Alice, so we didn't go to Sunday school, and we were playing around and I got up against a tarred fence somehow or other, got all tar on my frock - stood four o'clock on a Sunday afternoon washing me frock out 
in the horses trough. You can imagine what that was like can't you? Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What happened when you got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - father nearly went mad. Oh he didn't hit me, I think he was so furious that - I still went to auntie's to tea though - in another f
rock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they know that you'd missed Sunday school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
They didn't know until the Vicar found I come round and saw them. That boy got killed in the 1914 war. Yes. He lived next door, he was - nice kid. He went out in the 1914 war, got killed - 1915. Was only about eighteen too. Nineteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Or did one have a more important influence?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, both of them really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Not a great deal. There was - usually some little present was - bought for us. Might be a little doll or something like that. Mostly a doll because doll's were very cheap those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Mother might make a cake or father might make a small cake for us and - probably have one or two little kids in from a lot of streets you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well we normally spent Christmas Day at my grandmother's - at my mother's mother's. Used to go up there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 This was in Stepney?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. We used to go up there on the Christmas Eve night and they'd probably keep it up fo
r nearly a week in those days. And - family were all there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How many brothers and sisters did your mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Two sisters and - three brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So it was a large family party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And you used to stay overnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes
, we used to stay. Stay perhaps two or three days. Then had snapdragon and the Christmas pudding would be lit up and all that sort of thing. What they call snapdragon - they used to put - dried fruit in a dish you know and pour - I don't know whether it w
as brandy or whisky on it and set light to it you know and we'd all grab you know, grab a handful and perhaps there'd be some three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 penny pieces in it saved over from the Christmas pudding. Yes, lovely. Turn the light out and then light it all up in a big dish. Do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have Christmas trees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, oh yes, we always used to have Christmas tree, and - I think most of the children those days would join a club with a sweetshop and put a ha'penny or penny on it and buy the sweet decorations to h
and on the Christmas tree, something they could eat probably.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, all sorts of games they used to get up to. Postmans knock and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Singing - oh yes, everybody had a - if you could sing or - say a - poem or something like that, you'd all take your turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you enjoy Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Used to love it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have any musical instruments in your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Rather funnily we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. Yes. He was a very good singer but - and he was step dancer too, he was a step dancer, yes, oh he was a very good step dancer. I don't know whether he could ever play a musical instrument - I remembered him talking about a piano 
once but never in my lifetime. My grandmother had a piano but - we didn't have one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could anybody else in your family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 My sister older than me could, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, we'd sit and sing you know between ourselves and that sort of thing. I still sing so - I've always had a very good voice. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You sing in a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Anywhere, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you sang as well then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. When I was a kid I always got behind the chairs so nobody
 should see me. And I was scared rather funnily. This is - this is the part that's always amazed me, as a child I was a terribly shy child, never imagine it would you. Terribly shy, I'd go to my grandmother's and get under the table and all that sort of b
usiness and wouldn't come out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was singing important in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Very much so. Very - very much to me, still is. I love to get somewhere where I can sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you just sing around the house and would you all sit down some evenings and you sing to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
We'd sit down and sing and - I always used to go up and sing the kids to sleep, I used to. But - we used to sing around the house. My mother couldn't sing, but - oh I'd get out of bed singing in the morning. Yes. It's rather fun
ny really, I don't know - well I suppose - I always say it's the Welsh blood that's in me somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well there wasn't many games those days, you know, to play. Noughts and crosses and that sort of thing
, ludo and snakes and ladders, those sort of things we - we always had in the house, dominoes. Not cards very much, father and mother used to play a game of crib but - we wasn't allowed to play cards, except snap, we used to buy the snap cards, those. But
 - the ordinary cards we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about outdoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh, skipping and - and running.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father or mother ever play any outdoor games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Father - father used to like to go to football, I must say he used to take me - oh
 I'd play football with the boys and cricket when I was a kid. And - I was a tomboy and - running, I was very very good at running, I could run like a hare, if I'd have had the opportunity those days that the youngsters have got today I probably would hav
e got somewhere with running because I was a very swift runner. But - I always say I wore my legs away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you yourself liked outdoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, yes. Very fond of outdoor games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, we always books in our house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No. Newspapers - we only had the Sunday newspaper and we dare not touch that as children. If I wanted to read - read the newspaper I'd sneak it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I don't know, you know, old - the older - wel
l my parents generation, they didn't believe in children reading newspapers, they thought they were - weren't the fit thing for them to read. Don't think they are today do you? Yes. Yes. Yes. We were not allowed to read newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
There wasn't many magazines about in my day, there was the - oh The Christian Weekly, I remember that, that was a sort of a - it was a magazine but had a - more of a religious outlook, we used to have that indoors. Of course mother couldn't read
 and so of course she never bought books. I used to go to the library and get children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
s books. I used to go up to the library - get Dickens and that sort of thing, I used to love Dickens when I was a kid, used to read Dickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You said your father read to your mother quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes, he would - he would get - bring books in and read to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - well my mother died in 1912, father died in 1915. My grandf
ather died in 1914. And I remember a couple of aunts dying when I was a kid and - everybody went in deep black crepe and everything el}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 e - even the - even the babies them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you tell me a little bit about any of the funerals you can remember, who attended or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well - well if it was a case like when my mother died - of course there was father, an there was my two older sisters - myself and a younger sister, not the two little ones didn't go. My mother's sisters, her brother - one br
other went, her other two brothers were in the Army - her father didn't go because it was - quite an old man then, 'cos my grandfather was - a lot older than my grandmother. He - grandfather didn't go but - most members of the family went and of course th
ere - there was horses and - and they used to have big black feather things on their hea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 s and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 The horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, used to have black - big black - black velvet put over their - you know - bodies and - according to how much you paid for the funer
al there was four horses to the hearse and all this, if you only had two horses it was reckoned to be a very poor funeral and all the rest of it. And then they had on top of the hearse itself great big feathered things, I expect you have seen pictures of 
t
hem. Great big feathers all - if people had the money they had them, you know, put them on. And of course everybody wore deep black - ear - black ear rings and black necklaces and brooches and - wide black crepe on the bottom of their dresses, that sort o
f thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Veils?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. Veils they'd have. And even the children would - even - I always remember my youngest sister, she was three and she was very very fair, she had - very blonde hair, and my grandmother made our two black - made our black and
 - I always remember my - when my grandmother put her little black dress on I said, oh doesn't she look lovely grandma? Grandma took a dim view didn't she. She said, lovely, she said, in black for her mother? I don't think so. Very haughty. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So this was very strictly regarded that people wore black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes, yes. And you wore black - I - I - I know I put a coloured dress on, my mother had been dead about eight months, I put a coloured dress on and went over to my grandmother's. She said, get 
home and take that off at once. Wear black for twelve months. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Even children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Get home and take it off at once. Oh dear. She was an autocrat my grandmother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have lots of carriages or just the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well it's all ac
cording the size of the family and how much insurance money you'd got or how much money you'd got to spend you see. I think we had two if I can remember my mother's funeral, yes, two there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was it a big ceremony, would all the neighbours come out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, the neighbours all come out and all hang round the door I mean, today they don't do that quite so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Then you'd go to the church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Then go to the church and go - but of course my mot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 her and father were }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 buried over at the City o
f London Cemetery which in those days was a long way away. So I mean it was a long journey for Custom House to there so that people - there wasn't many people - only relatives that was over at the cemetery. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What happened after the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh well there was usually a big tea set out. And in those days they used to stop at - there was always a gig pub on the corner near the cemetery, there still is, a big concern opposite Grange Road cemetery, and outside the Ilford cemetery or City of Londo
n as it's called, there used to be a big pub called the Pig}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
ons, still is, it's still there and they used to - no, the Rabbits, sorry, Rabbits, and they used to come out there and you'd see all the coach - coaches outside lined up, people had been inside h
aving a drink. Those people of course who wanted a drink. 'Course we weren}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
t allowed to go in and have a drink - we were left in the carriages 'til they came out. This was stopped during the 1914 war when they started closing the pubs at three o'clock in t
he afternoon. Yes, you see before the 1914 war pubs were open all day long. They were open from six o'clock in the morning 'til eleven o'clock at night. So that - they sopped this during the 1914 war, I think in 1915 this was stopped. So this gradually so
rt of dropped off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And then everybody would go back to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Go back to the house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they come back to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, they all came back to our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Who prepared the tea then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 A neighbours, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, no. Oh no. A couple of the neighbours came in and did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was this regarded as a light}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5205790\charrsid16671506 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 hearted occasion afterwards or was it all still very serious and mournful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I think - well in the case I don't know with my mother I m
ean - they were all terribly - so terribly all upset because she was only forty-four you know, she was quite a young woman wasn't she. And they were all so terribly upset about it. And of course we'd had this terrible strike that had been on for weeks and
 weeks that nobody never had anything really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You said your father died three years later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. In '15 - 1915.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And he was fifty-three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He was fifty-three when he died. He was quite a young man really wasn't he, at fifty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Relations, we used to go and visit relations, not so much neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother or father take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Mother and father together. Mother never - mother used to go once now and
 again over to Stepney because she had difficulty on trams you see. Yes, it was trams those days, there wasn't very many buses and she - it meant her going on a tram or going by train and - if she went by train of course there was the stairs to climb and 
i
t was quite a walk from the station to her mother's house so it was easier to go by tram which meant her going on two trams, she had to go from Freemasons Road to Stratford, then from Stratford to Mile End. So that she didn't go a great deal. Grandmother 
used to come over to see us more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well actually I used to do most of the shopping for mother and - and if of course - I used to go with her to carry the bag as much as anything because she couldn't carry very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You did sometimes go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember going on any outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Never went on outings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, we used to go down to the - what we called the barge house down at
 Woolwich, they used to have a funfair down there, it used to be quite a days outing at Woolwich you know. We used to go to the - get off of the train at Woolwich and walk through the Woolwich gardens and - and it was all open there then of course they bu
ilt factories there after - but when I was a little girl there was the - the Barge House pub was there, I think it's still there. I believe it's still there, and - yes, it was like going to the seaside really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No. Never had a holiday until - when did I have a holiday - first holiday I ever had - when my husband was in the Army and I went to Saxmundham - he was stationed at Saxmundham and I went - spent a few days there with him. First holiday I ever went on.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well Saturdays was usually there was certain amount of work to do in the home on a Saturday and - go shopping you know, go with mother shopping, and dad shopping and fetch - dad and mum used to go out shopping together mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 That was a working day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well Sunday was religiously kept - we went to Sunday school three times on a Sunday. Yes. Yes, morning afternoon and evening, we used to go to children's service in the morning, Sunday school in the afternoon and children\rquote 
s service of evening. So that - I used to hate Sunday when I was a kid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have special clothes for Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Wore our ordinary clothes on a Saturday. We got a new frock on a Christmas and that was kept for Sundays all through the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well, just the - not outside, you wouldn't go and have a ball or a skipping rope r
 anything like that on Sunday, not Sunday, just didn't do that - went for a walk if it was summertime like - you know - used to have the band in the park and you could go out and listen to the band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But you could play games in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Play games in the house you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. Definitely. If I had a button off of anything or a piece of tape and I went to put me clothes on and found it was off and I used to sneak in - perhaps
 to the bedroom to put - stitch it on and my father would jump straight away, where's she gone, got some tape that she wants stitching on? She's got six days of the week, she's got to do it on the Sunday? That's what it used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you generally do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well you - you generally saw that you didn't - things didn't need a tape on. But if they did happen this is what he - I never remember my father going to church rather funnily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. And yet we were brought up - so strict in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What denomination were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Church of England. But we were very high church. I often think somewhere that - in my father - on my father's side of the family they might have been a - Catholics. Bec
ause - he - as I say, he never went - he never - the only time he went to church was to a wedding or a funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. We used to have Sunday school - and - I don't ever remember going to Sunday school outings when I was a kid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there any other social activities organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well they'd have a little - fete day you know, and we used to go round and have races and that sort of thing. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. I - I actually - though I was church of England I went to Congregational church really to get in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When you were older?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When I was - no, when I was quite young, I was the youngest member of the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you went to the Congregational Sunday school and church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
And church, I went to both. You see, I went to both, I used to go to - I used to go to Victoria Docks Mission actually, I was in their choir and I used to - used to go round to different other churches you know, to - sing Cantatas. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have any annual treats with the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No. Not - not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you just used to go round singing at other places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. That's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, they had a Ba
nd of Hope, I belonged to the Band of Hope for years. It used to be a scramble to get here because I had to wash up before I left, and father didn't get in 'til half past five, and Bank of Hope was six o'clock so if father didn't hurry up with his tea I d
idn't get to Band of Hope because I couldn't go 'til I'd washed up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 This was before the evening service then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did that club have any activities, evening classes or outings or treats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 The Victoria Dock Club did but I never went to any of those, I used to go to St Luke\rquote 
s church, Victoria Docks, and they used to have little clubs for youngsters. And on a Monday evening they had a Dorcas Guild and I used to go there with one or two more girls and thread the needles for the old ladies b
ecause they didn't have glasses like they've got today and we used to thread their needles for them, used to-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, not really. I - I belonged to a - I suppose - what would you call it - ph
ysical training club, they used to have a - a Presbyterian church on the corner where I lived at one time and it didn't matter what denomination you was you could go in there and join the - the club and you had sort of physical training.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And grace was said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Father would say - we would have to say it with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, not really but we always - say our prayers before we went to bed. Always said the, you know, downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Your father took an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well he was very much of a Socialist. His parents were - were Conse
rvatives. But he saw so much suffering in Stepney as a boy which him made him go the other way. He - he saw so much of this - he used to talk about Doctor Barnado's and the way he founded his homes and that sort of thing and the terrible suffering of thes
e children that were left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So he held his political views because of his experience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes, yes, yes. And he was a staunch trade unionist, he was in trade unions from the time I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he think that working men had a square deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh no, he - he was - constantly fighting for better conditions for - for working man. Well they didn't have a square deal, let's face it, I mean in those days, I mean - a man'd get a days work in the docks, he might not get another days work for t
wo or three weeks, and there was no other income you know, not in those days, nobody got anything, there was no - National Assistance or Public Assistance. If they give a woman what they called Parish Relief in those days it was either because the man was
 
sick in hospital - and the woman was unable to work. If a woman was left a widow she got a shilling for each child and a loaf of bread. That was all she got, nothing for herself. So she had to find work and - and - they used to - some of the women, their 
-
 their work was terrible in those days, I mean, ships cleaning, scrubbing ships paint in most terrible conditions of cold and everything else. But they were glad to do it. They'd go round finding work, even scrubbing doorsteps for - people say in the West
 
End who - didn't get them done. Taking in washing and even a mangling, if they had a mangle they would charge a penny a dozen or something like that dor doing somebody's mangling. And - and if they were known to have a mangle and they wanted - they - they
 
were on Parish Relief they would take so much away from them, and if a Relieving Officer come into the house and you had a vase or anything that could be sold, oh you can sell that, you can sell that picture, before you got anything. Yes. And to get this 
s
hilling and - and this loaf of bread - they used to have to walk all the way to - which is now - Langthorn hospital - that used to be the Union when I was a little girl, and they used to have to walk from south of the Borough all the way over there becaus
e
 they couldn't afford to ride, to pick up this shilling and a loaf of bread. I used to go with a girl who's mother was left a widow with about six kiddies and - I used to go with her. The kids used to you know, and we used to go for company, go right over
 there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You were allowed to go and collect it for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I - I used to go with them you know. Just - yes, yes, she'd go with her mother and I used to go with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 The Labour party as we know it now wasn't started until later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 1000.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your father involved in it from the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. He was in it, yes, and he was in the - well I used to go occasionally when I was a little girl so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Which union was he in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 He was in the General Municipal Workers Uni
on and in the - number one branch, he used to - I used to go and pay his union money at the Flying Scub pub in Blackburn Street, it's still there as a matter - that started in the public hall, Will Thorn stated that trade union, or that branch anyway.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I don't think so really. I think the mere fact that she couldn't read you know was a great drawback to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember your father voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. I can remember him voting in general election, and I know he voted Labour too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh they did, they did. Oh they did, yes, they di
d. Of course - being that my father worked in the docks I don't suppose that come into it, but I think and employed if he knew that men were sort of - they were called agitators straight away, they weren't sort of classes as trying to get better condition
s, they were victimised because of their - agitation for better conditions. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Your father was signed up member of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember him working for one of these parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I don't, yet I know th
at he was interested because I know - on the night of the elections I - I remember going out with him and my mother once and - we were waiting you know to see the results. And I think the opposition man's name, if I can remember rightly, was Elliston. And
 I - I think that was the time of Jack Jones election. And Jack Jones and Will Thorn. So I wasn't very old you know when they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I don't know, he used to go out, you
 know, he used to say well he was going to a meeting and I never used to bother where it was, I never - no interest in it, probably if I'd have been older I might have said, you know, and - but I new he used to go to meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You said you could remember very clearly the general strike in 1912?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
This is - that wasn't a general strike, in 1926 was a general strike. Yes, 1926 the general strike was when everybody came out. And - that was when Ernie Bevin advised them to go back, caused the bloodshed
. But in 1912 - I'm trying to think how that originally started, I think it was the miners came out first and then the railway men came out. Then of course the docks came out. And they were out for weeks. They were out for weeks. I remember a couple of ri
o
ts in - round by Custom House station. But people were starving, there was no question of it, they were starving. There was no food, there was nothing coming in, nobody gave them - there was no National Assistance or - relief. And - unions would appeal fo
r
 funds and probably those people who were not out on strike would give so much to the funds and there would be a few strike tickets as they called them issued perhaps at the end of the week. Tickets for food, that would be vouchers you know, about three a
n
d sixpence or three shillings at the end of the week for somebody to give you - and there would be a certain amount of them to go round. I know the day my mother was taken ill se never had only - never had a crust of bread in the house. And a we were wait
i
ng to see if there was any strike tickets that afternoon and my mother - on the Sunday morning the Secretary of the Branch of the Union came down and knocked and gave father some and I - 'cos shops were open on a Sunday then - and I went down on the Sunda
y morning and got a piece of meat and some bread and stuff.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How long did this last for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh I think it was about eighteen or twenty weeks that strike. Terrific time. Some of the churches got - soup kitchens as they called it, and gave the childre
n some sup and a cup of cocoa and a slice of bread for their breakfast. But I - was too old to get that because I was fourteen. So you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did people do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I - I - just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father do any music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, not then because h
is health was breaking, unfortunately, and - well people just pawned and sold everything they had. This was just it. So that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they go to meetings a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, there was meetings, there was - yes, they had open air meetings and of course t
he police would move them on sometimes and this would cause - perhaps - perhaps a riot like you'd get today. Not quite so vicious of course. But they tried to dispose of them because the men - probably would get out of hand, but let's face it, they had so
mething to get out of hand for. I mean, if people starving and they've got children starving - this is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 It must have been very much affecting this neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh shocking, yes. Yes. Specially - the south side you know down - all from here and downwards, those - the docks. Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When your parents weren't doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well, mother couldn't do very much because of her - her being paralysed, but if father was home he used to read to her and t
hey did used to play crib quite a lot and dominoes. Well of course in those days there wasn't other amusements, I mean there wasn't television or wireless or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they ever go out to enjoy themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes - my father had been a music hall turn in his younger days and he did used to take mother to the music hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she ever go out on her own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Not a great deal, she could go out on her own but she didn't go a freat deal on her own. She would visit my grandmother occasionally. But - ot
herwise - and of course she would go for a bit of shopping and I would go with her because it meant I - as little as - when - what - quite a youngster I had to carry the bag - carry the baby if there was one. That sort of thing. But she wasn't a woman tha
t went a great deal on her own. She had a friend she used to visit and the friend used to visit her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would the friend visit when your father was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, yes, she would come there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh use
d - oh he used - he used to go up for a drink now and again - he was in the Buffaloes, that was a - organisation and he - of course his trade union, he used to attend his trade union meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What was The Buffaloes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well it was a kind of a charitable organisation, more - it was more like at - a min}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13251636\charrsid16671506 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 atur}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13251636\charrsid16671506 e - or a working mans Freemason}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ry. That's the only way you could describe it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was this weekly or monthly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Weekly. Meet weekly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well not - when 
I was young, he - he had been a sportsman in his younger days - very young days. I used to hear him talk about boxing and - and that sort of thing, and running.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Or did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No. He wasn't a gambler in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No. Oh yes, once they did when I was about eight years - between about eight and nine years of age my father belonged to what they called the Farthing Club. They start at a farthing and went o
n 'til the end of the year, doubled it each week. And he was Secretary of that at one time. And that was held upstairs in a pub. But otherwise, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you get on with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well the younger ones very well, the older ones I didn't s
ee very much. My eldest sister and my grandmother brought up, when my mother was taken ill it appears that she took the two children over, they were only babies. And when mother came out of hospital mother took the younger one ho- e but the older one stay
e
d with grandmother. And lived with her for - right up until she was married. So I didn't see much of her. And then the older one, when she was about fifteen, wanted to go into service and this my father was very much against, he was a bit of a - a Sociali
st and he didn't believe in his children being - servants to other people. And he - he was against it, but she was so keen on going that he provided her with her clothes and let her go. So I didn't see a great deal of her, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she stick to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes. Yes, she stayed in service. And yet that - she really had a very good voice and - she did go to go on the stage but - she went on for a little while as a girl but - she never liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You all had good voices then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you feel particularly close to any of your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well - the younger ones, yes, because I brought them up you see, the younger - the youngest was three and a half and there was one five and a half, and the youngest one had had polio - of course those days
 it was called infantile paralysis and she was rather badly paralysed in the left leg and I had to take her backwards and forwards to hospital. I took her backwards and forwards to hospital before mother died and then I had to continue with it. And we are
 
still very close together now even today. So that - and then the other sister that was three years younger than me, she went to live with an auntie when I was - when she was three years old and she stayed with her until she was married. Well we were very 
attached at one time but we don't see - very much of one another today, we keep in touch, yes, I ring her up on the phone and - she sometimes rings me and - but we keep in touch but at one time we were very very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Is that Emily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well most of the children outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, or the - in those days we had fields quite near us so that we - this sounds amazing today doesn't it. We - we had fields quite n
ear us in Custom House and we used to go up the Brixham Road and pick buttercups and daisies. Cancied we was in the country. Doesn't sound feasible today does it. Yes. Used to go to the park and - play over there and we used to go up to the fields along B
rixham Road and - as I say - pick buttercups and daisies listening to the - birds singing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you go into each other's homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, as children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - hoops, five stone - cherry - we used used to ca
ll 'em cherry hobs, cherry stones you know, get a piece of cardboard and draw a - cut a whole it it and we used to put numbers on it and if you get - well - whichever hole you got it into, say it was five, well - your opponent had to give you five of his 
cherry stones or her cherry stones. But these - and of course skipping, we used to do a lot do skipping those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And ball games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, we had quite a lot of ball games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, I was allowed to get - and believe me I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. Yes, I was but of course I wasn't allowed out - during the winter when it was dark I wasn't allowed out after tea. In the summer yes, 'til about eight 
o'clock. I never went to bed early as a child, I always stayed up with my mother rather funnily. If father was often out at a night, I - out at night either working or some - or other and I remained up with mother. But when father was at home then I went 
to bed about nine o'clock. So - I was very attached to my mother, very much so. I suppose it was because I had to do so much for her really, that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You had very close contact with her from when you were tiny?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Well from a babe - from a little mite I somehow was bought up to realize that she was afflicted and she had to have help. So that -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And you were the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 That was born after she was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes, I was the eldest one after she was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, I used to to be - I - I went to the - we had the Y.W.C.A. at one of the chapels, I - actually I was Church of England but I used to go to this chapel and I was in their choir, I was the youngest one in their choir, an
d we used to go to different chapels, you know, and give a concert, cantata as they called it, and this I thoroughly enjoyed and there was another - on one of the streets where we lived there was another - well it was a Presbyterian Church on the corner a
nd they had a type of a youth club for the kiddies all around and we used to have - P.T., and - we called it drill hose days, we didn't call it P.T., we used to have drill and we used to have little concerts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You enjoyed sport didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. I loved it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have any hobbies, did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I used to do all sorts of funny things. I used to get walnuts and scrape the inside out and make pin cus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13251636\charrsid16671506 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ions of them. Make furniture ou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13251636\charrsid16671506 t of chestnuts with pins and w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ool.
 All these sorts of little things really. Yes. Things that one doesn't see today at all. With walnuts. Scrape the walnuts - the inside out, of course you'd eat that wouldn't you - and - stuff it with a little bit of sawdust. You press the material in with
 
a little bit of glue and it used to make little pin cushions. And of course - before Christmas you'd sit and make chains out of paper, you never bought chains, you bought the paper and sat and - sat and made the chains, so that kept us occupied a few even
ings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you found quite a lot to do in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, I think really that we did more those days than the children do today. The children today want everything found for them. We made things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You had some pets as well didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes, we had rabbits, yes, and we had - always had a cat and a dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No. Oh I say no, we - I used to go with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13251636\charrsid16671506 
 the kids and we used to go tidd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ler catching as we called
 it, with a jar and a - and a pin or something like that, used to go up - Invicta Road because there was quite a number of ditches up there, we used to call it the swamps. There still is. And we used to - but more so those days. Of course where the West H
am Stadium is today that was all ditches all along there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 It was quite a long walk up there for you wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh that was nothing, that was a short walk compared to what we did do. I mean we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you go walking a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well - yes. Oh - we used to go to - penny return to Woolwich on the train, more often than not we b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13720247\charrsid16671506 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
ught - we - we rode there and walked back, spent the ha'penny. And then - then from Woolwich we would walk to Bostal Woods which was a terrific long walk. That was our days outing of a holiday time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Just the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Just the children, not - no, oh no, no grown ups. Sometimes my mum and dad would take us to the Barge House at Woolwich. And that was quite a - an event because they had a fair there, w
e used to go through the Woolwich Gardens and down to the river, it was like going to the seaside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You took part in sport because you liked running?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Running, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever go to any music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I did, yes, I used to go to - go with mum and dad at times to a music hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, not as such, perhaps a ha'penny here and there you know, not - never got a regular pocket money.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If you had any what would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well sometimes if - if I - I used to take a couple of - lads dinners down to the factory because there wasn't canteens them days like there are today and I used to take their - their dinner down and - their mother would have given me sixpence a week. Well
 out of that I would buy my stockings and - you know - little odds and ends. Probably give it to mother and have a penny left or something like that. And of course - it'd go to excursions you know, save up for Sunday school excursion, we'd give a ha'penny
 
a week perhaps for that, work out about sixpence you know, go to Chingford or one of those places. Yes. That sort of thing. And then Christmas time to our Christmas party, we'd pay another ha'enny a week - Band of Hope we used to call it, which was temper
ance society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have to pay for all the Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Pay, yes. Just - it was just sixpence you know, take sixpence and that covered your fare and your tea and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did anybody outside the home help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Only my - my grandmother used to make some of our clothes because she was a very good dressmaker, and she would make some of our clothes. But rather strangely mother was very good at cutting out, she could only cut out with her left hand, and she wo
uld - I say cutting out, she couldn't cut out herself but she would draw - she would - have the material laid on the table and she would draw the h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720247\charrsid16671506 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 pe on it and I would have to cut it out. And she would pin the material to her dress and s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720247\charrsid16671506 aw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
 it that way. Sh
e was really - she had been a very good tialoress, so that she'd - know all that - well, all ways of cutting out material. But it was rather - yes. And it was rather a funny thing, I never interested myself in it in those days. I ought to have been a god 
dressmaker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When your mother was ill who helped }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720247\charrsid16671506 look}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  after}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720247\charrsid16671506  the home and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well the only time my mother was ever ill as I remember she - was when she had a baby, you know, like, 'cos I - I wasn't born when she was paralysed. But - my - my si
ster May who was - about nine years younger than I was - when she was born I was away at country holiday. We used to go for country holiday from school, that - that organisation still exists today rather funnily, to give children a holiday. We used to pay
 
four and tuppence those days. For the holiday. And we used to have a fortnight. Well I was away on - holiday when my sister was born. And I think one of the neighbours looked after mum then. But when my youngest sister was born I was kept at home from sch
ool and I did the housework and - a neighbour did the washing but I did all the housework and the cooking. And I think I was about - eleven when she was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And you'd already been helping a lot so you knew what to do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your parents see much of their relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Father never had any relatives. His - his father died when he was quite a young man and his mother died when I was about - five and he was an only child. There were some cousins somewhere but I - didn't kno
w them. But - mother used to see quite a bit of her relatives, her sisters used to come down and see her, and her brothers. Her brothers more so than her sisters rather funnily. And of course her mother used to come down to see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, not really, mum - she made friends with the neighbours you know, just around but - they had one or two special friends that 
used to come and visit and we used to visit them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would they he offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. If we had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about neighbours, did neighbours come in much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, I think they did - we - one or two neighbours used to come in to mum, one neighbours especially mum used to rather - strange}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13720247\charrsid16671506 ly my mother used to help}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  look after her children because - she was a woman that did drink. She was a ver
y nice woman but - unfortunately this was her failing. And mother, rather than see her get into trouble with her husband, I - sent me in to clean up for her you know. Yes. And - she thought a lot of my mother really. But I think people those days were mor
e neighbourly you know, you don't get it today. If anyone was in trouble the neighbours would - would rally round and - and they were all in the same position. You see, but you 'don't get it today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 People often tell us in those days people made their own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh well they did more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What would grown ups do among themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well of course - if you never had a piano you - perhaps sometimes some - somebody played a whistle or an accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4393050\charrsid16671506 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 n or something like that. Gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4393050\charrsid16671506 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 phones were in - we didn't call 'em - or phonographs they called them in those days you know, they were cylinders, you know, the round ones. And I know it used to amaze me, we did have a gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4393050\charrsid16671506 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 phone when I was a kid for a little while and I remember sitting over 
that thing puzzling where the voice came from. This always puzzled me as a child, I couldn't understand how the voice comes through - 'cos they was horns on them - how the - how the voice came through this horn I could never - never fathom that out. Not a
s
 a little children, it was - something funny to me. And we used to have - you know, they'd go in one another's houses, if they were friends they'd have a - I mean they could buy a gallon of beer for a shilling in those days and - and they'd have a collect
i
on between them and probably buy a gallon of beer or half a gallon of beer and go round someone's house on a Saturday evening. And if the people who they went to had got it they'd have - they'd have sandwiches and have - they'd all sing a song each you kn
ow, and - they made their - yes, they made their amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. I mean - when I we
nt friends with a girl for a number of years who's father owned the bakery, you know the grocery shop, and he - he was a baker himself and employed people and they, in those days, were what you'd call middle class. And - I mean today shopkeepers - no, no 
- not the ordinary shopkeeper is just an ordinary working man practically, but in those days - if you - you owned a business of that description you were of course middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Middle class tended to be the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What other classes would you have thought there were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well of course the ordinary working class were ordinary working class those days, no question of it. We were working people and they were people who were - - playing to get work to live, because otherwise there was no means of e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4393050\charrsid16671506 x}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4393050\charrsid16671506 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
tence, if you didn't have work you - you went without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there any other classes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well no, I wouldn't say that, of course doctors and those sort of people again you would call middle class these days. So that
 - of course the higher class - well those sort of people we didn't see down this end of the town at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would you have divided the working class up into other groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well of course - there was - there was a certain amount, you see, you got th
e - some working class people - tried to - to keep themselves very nice and - others - didn't bother. I suppose times were so bad that they lost interest in everything. That was the trouble. Then of course you - you got the - people who went round with a 
b
arrow and that sort of thing, you cost - call them costermongers. They were the salt of the earth but they were crude you know in their talk and - and in their way of - way of living, some of them - some of them could be spotlessly clean, others could be 
the reverse, but se've still tot those type of people today unfortunately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. My father was very adamant on this. We were taught that everybody was equal and
 - if it was a tramp knocked at the door for a glass of water, which could happen in those days, tramp knocked at the door and asked for a glass of water - I couldn't go in and say to my father, there's a man - or there's a tramp knocking at the door. He 
w
as a gentleman. We were taught this. And if it was a - a poor old woman hawking something, coming along with a basket perhaps little bit of cotton and stuff in and kocked at the door I had to say there was a lady at the door. And we were brought up very s
trictly in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you ever told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No, my father wouldn't have this, he said you - you bow the knee to no man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I don't remember, only when I went to service for a
bout three months and I detested it. I went to service for three months and detested every day of it. Rather funnily - I wanted to go but - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Which class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well this is rather difficult because my father had to wor
k for his living but in his younger days his parents had been in a - fairly comfortable position really, I wouldn't say middle class, but afairly comfortable and my grandparents on my mother's side had their own business, my grandmother had her own busine
ss, grandfather had his, see, so that - they weren't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you think people thought about classes much?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
I don't think they did quite so much. The only thing that they did think about the working class themselves was so terribly oppressed that to 
them the upper class were - were just something out of this world, they - you know, realized - they were beginning - people were - were beginning to realize that they were bring - being oppressed, and they were those days, there was no question of it. The
y were oppressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 In this area who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I don't really know, not in our area, not really. The clergy, the - the - sort of looked up to, the doctor was looked up to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Who would the doctor associate with for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Usually clergymen and - people in - in businesses who had, you know, quite a good business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Teachers again yes, they were more of a - a middle class, and yet your teachers in West Ham, some of them were Educ
ated in West Ham and took up teaching in West Ham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well mostly other teachers. And their own relatives of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What sort of people would you say went to the church and what went to the chapels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 We
ll I think they were the same type of people that went to the church and chapel, but you see mostly in most case the - they were again middle class people as much as anything. Of course some of us were - who went to church - we always felt that we were - 
something different in those day}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 s. Unfortunately this was - a t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 rait I suppose that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Of the church or the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes - yes - well I think of both. Both, yes. More so the church than the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where you lived did all the people in the 
working class have the same standard of living or would you have said there were different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Mostly - mostly - some were a little bit more f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 tunate than - than others where the man was working, in regular work and there was probably one or 
two group up children well then they were able to improve of their conditions. But on the whole people were almost the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you think that some people felt superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I - well sometimes one did get that but not very much - not very - not so much in those days as one gets it today I'm afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were some families thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes, there were some thought of as rough and some as respectable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could be, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Never. In fact my father was a man who would bring - bring anybody if he thought they needed a meal. And - it was 
nothing for me, when my father was working 'course my father was in regular work, it was only in latter years his health gave - but I mean when the money was coming in it was nothing for me to take kiddies in and they would be fed at the table and given a
 meal. Oh yes, yes. He wouldn't have no class distinction at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, if you - oh yes if you had the money you could move out and move somewhere else the same day I was going to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And that's how you moved up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you remember anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. I can remember people who did do this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you member anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, not in my younger days I can't. As I got older we had a lady come and worked down here in - in St Luke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 s Parish and she was a thorough lady. And - a natural lady, she really was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you explain what you mean by a natural lady?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well - she gave up her - her - she had a huge house down in Kent, she had money, and she gave up everything to come and work amongst the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh gosh, yes, they was always around - in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you think of him, what were they like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Most of them were all right you know, we - I always got on all right with the police, I suppose I 
never got caught out doing anything wrong, I don't know. But - I got on all right with the policeman, but we had an healthy respect to the policemen in those days. You see, if a policeman - if you were doing something wrong the policeman could clip you ro
u
nd the ear with him glove and you had an healthy respect of it. I don't know whether he - I - you know they say you're only - you're only punished if you're poor, well I never got caught so I suppose - why - but - I mean if one went over the park and - an
d a ball went on the grass, well the other one would look to see where the park keeper was before you got over and got the ball, because he'd got a cane then and you got a cane across your legs. And - I don't see where that was wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes, he used to call every Monday regular. And he was a man that when he was - explaining anything or talking to you, he - he used to come in with a saying, do you follow me? Well all us 
kids nicknamed him, do you follow me? It was the only name we knew him by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you know what your parents felt about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well, I suppose like most parents those days I think most landlords were the same those days. They didn't like
 doing very much to the places. Collected the rents but they didn't do much in the way of decoration or repairs, unless they had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So were they popular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not very. And again, if a person left a week or two weeks rent they would get the brokers 
in and take half their home away. I - I as a child can remember seeing many a home put out on the kerb - people made homeless. Not because they wouldn't pay their rent, because they couldn't pay it, they never had it to pays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And they just used to put it out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, and if another person took them in they was likely to get put out themselves. They used to take them in but of course in those days you could go from one place to another, it was - plenty of empty places about that one could go and get
. By virtue of the fact that people couldn't afford to pay much rent and they - packed in with one another you see. Living in one room and all that sort of thing. Eat and sleep and - everything else in one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But there was plenty of accommodation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, there was plenty of accommodation those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you remember being aware that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I used to think it was - I used to worry with my mother you
 see, she would say that she hadn't got money and all the rest of it and I used to know. In fact - I used to take myself out - up - without letting her know, up to my grand mother's and let my grandmother know that my father was ill and my grandmother wou
l
d know immediately there was no money coming in the house. And she would send out and get vegetables and groceries and piece of meat and - stitch a couple of shillings up in the lining of my frock, so that I shouldn't lose it on the way home. I used to do
 this without my mother knowing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh a great deal. Great deal. He was never really out of work, he was never unemployed, but of course he suffered with rheumatic go
ut and this piled up on him, he was losing a lot of work through - through illness and of course there was nothing coming in. If he went in the - if my mother hadn't have been paralysed they wouldn't have given her anything at the - what was it called - P
a
rish Relief those days, and I remember one time my father being ill and he wouldn't go into the hospital because it was the infirmary in those days and he wouldn't go it and they gave my mother four shillings for four of us, that was for her - a shilling 
f
or herself, shilling each for my two children and a shilling for me. So there was no rent allowance, nothing like that. For the week. Just four shillings. Well it varied. Of course things were cheaper those days, let's - I mean once could get a loaf for a
 penny three farthings or tuppence, you could get a pound of sugar for a penny three farthing. You could get a tin of milk for tuppence }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ha'pence or tuppence. Margarine was four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 pence a pound, butter we never saw. Cows milk we never saw. So that - fo
od was much cheaper, one could buy a joint for a shilling. In fact a small piece of flank of beef you could get for sixpence. But then again with all it's cheapness if the money wasn't coming in you still couldn't buy it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was four shillings regarded as quite generous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Not - well no - by the people who received it. The people who gave it thought it was generous but not for the people who received it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they come and inspect the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, and if you'd got to anything to sell you had to sell it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did they treat your mother when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well I went with my mother once, my mother was really - terribly upset and I was only a child and went with my mother once to the Relieving Officer and he shouted at her. And
 I said to him, don't shout at my mother, I said, you wouldn't shout at my mother if my father was here. I was so indignant, and I was only a child, I don't think I was more than ten. And - this is how they treated people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And you minded very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No, but father used to talk to me a lot about everyday events. He was - very good that, and if I read something in a book and I didn't quite understand what it meant I would ask him and he would explain. Mother couldn't read so she couldn't - help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Three years old. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you go a full day when you were three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes. They used to in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 From nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Nine 'til four in the afternoon. Nine 'til half past four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well the ordinary elementary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was it for girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Mixed. Mixed, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I only went across - I only had to go across the road when I was at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When you started at three who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 My mother went with me first. First couple of weeks I suppose, what happened we used to sort of attach ourse
lves to other children or they attached theirselves to us and - off we used to trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I liked it very much. At one period I thin
k when I was about eleven I - I had suddenly took a dislike to school. I don't think I was getting on too well, I - I had lost quite a bit of time through - mother having a baby and one thing and another and I think that - I went back you know, those days
 really if you lost time from school you did go back. And - I think it had a bearing that it made me that I suddenly disliked school, but I got out of that - phase and - matter of fact I didn't want to leave when it come to leaving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you go to the same school from the age of three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No. No. I - I went to that school 'til I was about four and a half and then I - of all things I contracted smallpox and - well it was a very big epidemic in this - in this area at that time and - three of the family 
had it. My mother had it, one of my sisters had it and then I got it. And - when I came back from the school - they hadn't got room for me and I went to a Catholic school that was nearby. I continued at that one for quite a period. And then we moved away 
and I went to a school further up the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Which school did you like best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I liked all of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you get on with the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 One or two teachers were very very nice, but we had one - one school I went to, one teacher. Sh
e was - she treated us very badly, all of us, not only me. But on the whole I got on fairly - go on with the teachers fairly well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they emphasise certain things as important, like punctuality?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Cleanliness - cleanliness and punctuality, our 
headmistress at one school, she would inspect our hands and our shoes and boots every morning to see if they were clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, we were taught that we'd got to know to speak properly. But then my father was very str
ict in the home with that too. And this is what I - I deplore today in children are - are given a good education, they got to grammar school and they come out with a - such expressions as my muvver, my favver and - this is - this is to me is awful today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 They're not taught to speak properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If you did anything that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh you'd get the cane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 For what sort of things would you get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh simple things, if you got sums wrong - really you know if you - you did things wrong. I don't remember ever getting the cane though. I don't know why, as I say I don't suppose they found me out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, I found that out too - sometimes you got a girl who probably a was a - people were a bit more com
fortable than the others and she was dressed a little bit different and - it wasn't the case all the time but you did get one or two teachers that would single these children out, probably they were dressed a bit a different than others. But on the whole 
the teachers were very good, especially if they found out - now I know the headmistress I had at one school, when she found out that my mother was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 paralysed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  she was awfully good to me. If I was a bit late for school she would know that I'd been to get the shopping. She was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not really I don't remember this. Don't remember the gang t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 pe that one gets today really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there any children who were left out of things? Were there any workhouse children for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No. No. Not really. Not - not at our schools there wasn't. I - I don't think any teacher - would tend to have children that because they never had anything be left out. They would try to get them all in. On the whole, whilst
 teachers were more stricter those - those days, they were very humane in most of their - they really knew that the children were having a hard life of it. And they tried to do their best for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Thirteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. I would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I - I was going to but my mother dying I was left with the younger children and this i
s something I've always regretted, even today, that I never had that opportunity to do part time education. Of course there were evening classes even when I left school. But I just couldn't go, 'cos I couldn't leave the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And your only regret about your education is that you couldn't have gone on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Couldn't continue, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well not really, but I used to go in and clean a woman's windows, I'd got - more nerve than I've got today. I used to go in and clean this woman's windows, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 fir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 st out upstairs and clean the outside and she'd give me tuppence for doing that 
and there I used to take two chaps' dinners to - to work and I used to get sixpence and my aunt, she did tailoring, she - and I used to take her work back to shop as we called it and she used to give me sixpence. But of course I used to ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 d that over to mother at the end of the week, probably get a penny back, but it - that went to buy my clothes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you earnt quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I was apprenticed to tailoring of all things and I detested it. Hated it
. Yes. Hated it. And I was there six weeks and I didn't want to know, I gave it up as a bad job. Wasn't interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I don't know, I think it was adver}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4406967\charrsid16671506 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ed somewhere or other, a board up somewhere I went after it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How much did they pay you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - about - half a crown a week and I had to buy my own cotton out of that. 'Cos I was being apprenticed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Why didn't you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Because I - no, because I'd seen so much of it in my life you see. I
'd seen so much, my aunt lived in the same house as us and I used to sit at the machine turning the pockets out of the trousers and the straps and I saw more trousers in my life than I ever wanted to see. I didn't want to know did I. And my mother said - 
of course mother had been a tailoress and her - her mother had her own workshop, and of course mother said I'd got to go and learn tailoring. I didn't want to learn tailoring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So what did you do next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Packed that up and went into a sweet factory.
 And father didn't like me working there because - it was a little bit on the rough side. Then I decided I wanted to go into service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How long were you at the sweet factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I don't know, about three months I think. And then I decided I wante
d to go into service. Father didn't want me to go, he was a - very much against it, but I wanted to go. All right, you can go. I was only there a month and I wanted to come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you tell me a little bit about your month in service?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Three m
onths I had in service. Well it was a house not very very far from here. And - including myself there was seven of us in family. I had to be up six o'clock in the morning, clean a huge fireplace. It was a six roomed house with a big conservatory built at 
the sides. I didn't have to do he washing but I had to assist with the washing. Clean windows, do every other work in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 All the cleaning of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, all the cleaning and it - there was some cleaning there to do believe me. And - t
here was there children and they were little horrors. Well I suppose I'd been brought up strict and these kids wasn't. And - I was given half a day off a week on a Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How much did you get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And I got half a crown a week. That -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you sleep there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I slept there, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have a room to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I slept in the same room as the - mistress's sister. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was there any other living in help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Oh no. The woman - like the mistress helped - she h
elped in the house of course. But I did the rough work, I mean - doorsteps and all that sort of thing had to be cleaned every morning early and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about cooking, did you have to do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I didn't do much with the cooking, she did the cooking I think. I did no cooking at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - fairly well really, the food was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did you eat your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 With them most of the time, but if they had any company well then they had it in their - i
n their parlour as they called it or - drawing room, whatever they like to call it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You had the same food as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, I had the same food, yes, I had very good good, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you have to call them, or call the mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes ma'am and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you feel she was interested in you as a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
She might have been but she was a little bit on the snobbish sise. You know, he had a - a business and - I think, you know, that she - she felt, you know, that she'd got to live u
p to this, well she could live up to it, there was no question of that. They'd been business people and I think they'd come from a business family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she try to give you any moral guidance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she mind what time you came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh I had to be in at ten o'clock after my afternoon off, that didn't matter because my father would have me in early, I wasn't allowed out father ten o'clock when I was at home. In fact up to the week before I was married I was going to say I had to b
e in at ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How old were you when you took this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh terribly. Yet I wasn't far from home, I could walk home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you have gone home in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, no, no I never went home in the evening time, just this half time an a Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was there anything you really hated about the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not really, I - I - because I - I liked housework and washing, I never - that never - part never worried me, I think it was being awa
y from home. This was the trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about the working part of it, was there a lot of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh there was quite plenty to do really to keep the house going because I mean it was a biggish house. And - it was kept nice. She liked it kept nice 
and - wasn't much to do of evening time, directly after the - you know - tea, used to wash up. There wasn't very much to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did you go and sit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I used to sit in the living room and - they probably would sit in their front room while 
I sit in the living room and there was - perhaps the children were there and I'd play with the children, you know, games that sort of thing, or sit and read or do a bit of sewing. Something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Then you were mainly homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. And I was only home a month - a month or six weeks - when mother died. So - 'course I didn't go out again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you do any work after you were in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, I worked at a - a there was a - people had a couple of shops of the main road and I went to wo
rk for them, and that was hard work. I used to have to be there well - half past six of the morning, sometimes half past nine at night before we got home. And - that was scrubbing and cleaning and - washing up to do. They'd got one little boy, and - I use
d to get a half a crown a week for that you know but - the money was poor in those days really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When you lived in did they entertain a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 They had quite a lot of people there, they used to have friends there and relatives used to come round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they have a very high standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not extraordinary. I - I would say - average really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 After your mother died you stayed at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes, all the time because I couldn't leave the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What kind of occupation would you have liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
I don't really know, I suppose I'd only been used to do the housework. Actually - when I was about seventeen I - I went part time, my youngest sister went away to Cahailey, to the arts and crafts school, only left the other one at 
home and she used to go to school and I used to do a part time job in the - in Relief kitchens. And of course that was helping with cooking and cleaning and - this sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What are these kitchens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well they cook - used to cook dinner - d
inners for invalids in those days, poor - people were glad of them. And they used to pay a penny for a very good dinner or a penny for a milk pudding and that sort of thing. They used to have to go there and collect it - no, they didn't have the meal ther
e, the meal was collected and taken ho e to whoever was the invalid. And there was only the cook and I that used to do it. And ladies used to come down voluntary and do the - taking the money and doing the books you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
I don't know, I don't think so. I don't think so. I went fulltime during the 1914 war and of course I was married then. And I went full time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I was working in Salto
wn Rubber Works at that time. Of all things making golf balls while war was on. Yes. But I was doing a man's work you see, I was doing work - women were doing the work that men had been doing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Have you worked since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 W
ell - not to go out to work in a factory or anything like that, I used to do washing and - take in washing to help out and I'd go to flats cleaning or - for one or two people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And during the last war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I was doing casualty service and auxiliar
y nursing. I did that - that was full time of course. I started doing it voluntary and then I went full time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Did you feel that were divisions of interest among people, were you interested in the relationships between workers and employers when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well I don't know about that, I always had an attitude that - if an employer wanted to get the best out of people they should have treated them different. You see, employers were more autocratic in those days, we were there to do a job an
d that's all they were concerned about. And - well if you'd have been a slave they would have had to have kept you and clothed you so - you wasn't much more really. There's a different relationship I think today. But there wasn't in those days, you were t
here to do a job and of course if you didn't do the job there was plenty waiting on the corner could come and take your place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you mind about this, how did you feel about it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I don't think I - I bothered about it in that - at that time. 
I thought a lot about it but never bothered about it. And - and of course I was a person that - if somebody said something to me I wanted to know why they said and I'd want to know all about it. I would answer back. I wouldn't be rude but I would answer b
ack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did this affect you when you were living in, did this cause problems?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well I think it could have done. I think it could have done. Maybe they didn't make it - they didn't let me see it was a problem but I think it was. As I say today I - I was a rebel all joy life and I'm still a rebel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did this working change your relationship with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you spend Sundays any differently when you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well actually my father died you know before I was eig
hteen you see, he was quite - I was quite young when he died. Hut - I - it was - I didn't go full time work until after he died. I was only doing part time. And I didn't go to work on a Sunday, so that - it wouldn't make much difference really, I was home
 in the afternoon before he came home - before my sister came from school. And - I used to do the work during the time I was home. And then of a Sunday of course he was there, and I was there, so it didn't make a great deal of difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No, not really. I - I didn't associate with a lot of people you see, that was the trouble, if I'd have worked possibly in a factory I would have done you see, but working - working in the invalid kitchens
 there was only the cook and I there that - I didn't associate with people very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you had the complete responsibility for the home when you were eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Before I was eighteen I was - I was under fifteen when mother die
d and father - went to work and I was just left in charge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you look after him when he was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, I had too look after him when he - 'course he - finally he was only in the hospital a week when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What age were you when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Eighteen. I - I was getting married when father died, I had to put it off. And - I got married a fortnight after he died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How long had you known your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - from about - from when I was about thirteen or fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well actually my husband was serving in a shop round the corner from where I lived. And I used to go in there and I was a cheeky little cat and I used to torment him and - and then he left there and I was going somewhere one d
ay and met a very old friend of mine that I went to school with and he'd got my husband with him and he introduced me. I said, I already know him. And - it was rather strange. About a week after I was coming home from church and there was a sand bin on th
e
 corner and this Tom said to me, what have you got in your hand? I said, a prayer book. He said, can I have a look at it? I said, yes, of course. So he said, oh the marriage service is in here. So he said, yes. Oh, he said, go and - go and stand round the
 back you two and I'll marry you. So I always say we were married twice. Strange wasn't it? And - that was it, we always went - went - you know, sort of gradually got friendlier and - that's what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh he only lived a few streets away from where I lived. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you save up money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Never had a chance. Never had any to save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I suppose about a year, I got engaged when I was seventeen, he bought me a ring and - we were engaged about a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well, it wasn't very much of a wedding, I'd just lost my father and - you see, there was just my husband and I, his sister, my mother's brother and his wife and - my husb
and's mother. But there was - of course the war was on, the 1918 war was on then, that was in 1915, and - the morning we were married there was, rather funnily, a soldier, sailor and a fireman were married that morning. Three of us together, and they were
 all in uniform, the men were all in uniform.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your husband in the services then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, he was in the Army. He had joined up. That's why we - we got married, because he was going - he knew he was going out to France. And he thought - by my - w
ell the fact that I was alone - you know, on my own, that - the - well his allowance would be a little bit of money for me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you still living at your father's home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh father was dead then, yes, I had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your younger sister still with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 One of them, the younger one wasn't - the younger - the youngest one was away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When did he go away again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 About three or four days after he went - went to France. And I never 
saw him for - thirteen months, he was out there thirteen months. My - eldest daughter was born nine months after and she was nearly six months old - five months old before he saw her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you continue to live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I - my sister went to live with my aunt and I went to live with my mother-in-law. I went there to live with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your husband away the whole of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - nearly all the time, he was out in - he was wounded in 1917, severely wounded. And my oldest daughte
r was taken ill with measles and pneumonia and meningitis set in and left her blind and paralysed and - at that same time he was officially reported missing, believed killed. But of course he was found and taken to hospital and they sent him to hospital i
n
 England, he was in hospital three months with seven gun shot wound and incidentally he never got a pension. Well then he came out of the hospital and they gave him a months leave and he was transferred to the - another Essex Regiment, he was in the Essex
 Regiment that was formed in West Ham during the war, then he was tra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7278003\charrsid16671506 nsferred to another Essex Battalion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
 and then they found him unfit for overseas service and he was transferred to the Suffolks. Then from the the Suffolks he was transferred to the First Ro
yal Dragoons, and he was in the First Royal Dragoons when he was discharged in 1919, he was in the Army the whole time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did he join up because of the war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7278003\charrsid16671506 Oh he voluntee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 red, yes, he volunteered, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And you had your daughter ill at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How old was your husband when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Had he been working in the shop until he joined the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, no, he left there and went to work in the paint factory down in Silvertown. Kingston and Johnson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7278003\charrsid16671506 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 s he worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What job did he do after he was discharged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well he went back to his same work but I - of course the slump came and - he was put off. And then he went to work in Tate's for a little while. And - of course - he wasn't long there 
because they were just putting the men off. And he worked at Lyles and then he - he went as Verger at our local church and - he was there for quite a while but the money was so bad and - he tried to get something else. And of course the complete slump cam
e when there were so many men out of work that he tramped all over the place, he - he and other men you know to get work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 This was in the '30's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 The '20's and '30's, yes. '20's and '30's. And then he finally went to work at Whipps cross hospital,
 well he had a very serious illness, he went back to the paint works rather strangely and whilst there he was taken ill with pleurisy and pneumonia and then pyema set in and he was very very ill, extremely ill for months. And after he came out of hospital
 
- they gave him - he got a job as a - an attendant in Whipps Cross for a short time and then he went to what was called the Central House, which is now today Langthorn. And he worked there, well then during the war a part of it was bombed and - they sent 
h
im back to Whipps Cross and he worked as an assistant gardener there. And then he had a severe abdominal operation and it got too much for him and - he went on - he he went as a gate porter on Forest House and he - did that work until he died - 'til he re
signed - or retired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Where's Forest House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Why it's in James Lane. This end of Whipps Cross. And he was working there up until he retired at sixty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 That's quite a long way to go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Was really. Oh yes it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You said you did odd jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did your husband feel about you working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
He didn't like it. Well of course it meant me - coming home or going out of evening time and doing a bit of cleaning, I used to go over the library and that sort of th
ing and - I say - say with taking in washing I mean I was ironing until late at night and - he never said much about it but he didn't like it, he said that I was doing too much. Which I really was. I mean, with a family and - to keep going it was really h
ard going, there's no question of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Which of his jobs do you think he enjoyed most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I don't know, he - he didn't bother about any of them, I think he enjoyed all of them really. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How many children did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I had twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Could you tell me the ones that were born before the end of 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Two. Yes, one born in 1916 and one born in November 19 - a week after the war finished - my Daisy was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Two girls then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Actually they - and they were bot
h premature. Emily was about three weeks, only three weeks, but Daisy was six weeks premature. Yes. Yes, I had this Spanish flu at the time and they - they were losing nine mothers out of every ten with it because the terrific high temperature they were r
unning and I had it. I don't know how I got over it, I was very very ill, extremely ill. And she - she of course was a premature through it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she survive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, she's fifty-two, that's Nadine's mother. Yes, the stout one. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And Emily is the one that became ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes, she's still alive, she'd fifty-four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did she ever recover?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Not fully. She didn't walk 'til she was nine years old, she wore napkins and had to be fed. And today one has to cut her food up for her. Sh
e's not mentally defective in the sense that she was born mentally defective, she's more of a spastic type, the brain doesn't co-ordinate with the - the body as the saying is. She talks quite sensible, but of course she can't do very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you look after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. Yes. I looked after her. Did everything for her, and all the other children. Yes. Took her backwards and forwards to hospital, tried every hospital I think - of course when I look back it was only wishful thinking, I knew in my h
eart that they couldn't do anything but like most mothers I thought that perhaps something could be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Nearly all - I only had two in hospital, all the rest were born at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. Didn't know the first thing about it when I was going to have my first baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you get on in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well not too bad, they'd just started opening the Welfare clinic, the maternity clinics, that year, and I went down
 there you know and then they started to - but I was really very ignorant on what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was this typical do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, it was those days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not really, only the - like, as I say, they'd st
arted the maternity clinic, I think I was about six months when they opened the first maternity clinic and that maternity clinic's still there today, in Elder Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How soon were you out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh wasn't allowed to put your foot outside the bed
 until the tenth day and then you was only allowed to sit up for an hour and go back to bed again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How long was it before you could get up completely?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well fourteen days near enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your mother in law look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, she looked after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 The nurses form the nurses home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you feed your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I nursed her myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you enjoy feeding her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. I nursed all my children. One of them was put on the bottle 
part time, oh no, two of them was put on the bottle part time because - when I had my Benny my mother-in-law died sudden and I - did quite a lot of funning about and it was only three weeks old and I - that tended me to lose my milk. But I kept him on but
 fed - partly fed him with bottles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have any difficulties in feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If you needed advice who did you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I always went - went to the clinic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If the baby was a sleep would you wake it for a feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If it cried before the normal time would you feed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What did you do if it didn't seem hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well I don't know, my kids always did seem hungry but I can't go back. I - I didn't I didn't believe in feeding them every five
 minutes but if - you know - they'd gone near enough to their time, it was only a short space before time and then I would feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When did you first give it solid food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 In those days you didn't give them solid food until they were nine mont
hs old. You - you could give them, we were recommended to give them - oh what do you call them - can't think of the name of them now - but they were like a kind of a biscuit. And we used to soak them in warm water and then boil the milk and pour on the mi
lk and a little bit of sugar and give them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When did you wean the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Nine months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How, sudden or gradual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh no, you - you'd - you'd sort of - you'd do it properly, you know, you - you'd start feeding them. That was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the baby mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh most times they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you think at the time that it did any harm to a baby to let it cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I don't know, I - I didn't think it hurt them not for a little while, but I didn't leave it - believe in letting them c
ry too long, I mean if you was in the middle of cooking a meal or something like that and you can't get something done - you've got to get it down for somebody coming in from work, well you had to let them cry for a little while, but - not too long.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your husband have much to do with the children when they were babies under a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, he - if I wasn't there, I was busy, he'd change them you know and that sort of thing. And in the case where the boy was partly fed he would make his bottle if I was busy you know and do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you manage for money when your husband was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh my God, I don't know. I - well I don't know but it - you see the first few months I was only getting, what - I think it was - twelve a
nd sixpence. My allowance, and then it went up to sixteen shillings. But my mother-in-law never took any rent off of me, she used to let me buy my own food but she never took any rent off me so I managed. And then when my Emily was six months old - five m
o
nths old, I went to work and she had the baby. And of course things were much easier. I got eighteen shillings when Emily was born and then it went up to twenty-one. And I started work, my sister-in-law worked in Silvertown Rubber works and she said there
 
was a vacancy, would I like it? And my - I said to my mother-in-law, well, what's going to happen to the baby? She said well she would have her. So I paid her for having the baby and we all lived in together then so that I paid her so much a week for my f
o
od and I did manage. And I put money buy and bought some home for when my husband came home because his money didn't go to it so that I didn't do too bad. I wouldn't say I was - very well off, I had to - sort of allocate my money out every week how much I
 
could afford to spend and how much I could - sort of live on and clothe the baby and myself on. And give my mother-in-law her money, and - and of course when I - I - I fell with my second baby and had to give up my work I got one room along the - one of m
y neighbours let me have one room and - I had a pretty hard struggle then. I managed but I had to - you know - work every ha'penny out that I - I couldn't waste a ha'penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 With the depression did you have this similar sort of situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Dreadful time that depression. We never went hungry, I won't say that and - we managed but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the parish help people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. You see, it became Public Assistance in those days and they helped people you see, and - if a man was gen
uinely unemployed he got a certain amount. But it was only just enough to live on and pay your rent, you did get your rent paid - that was a godsend. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they have the same attitude as in your mother's day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - well, one or two of them did
. One or two of 'em could be very arrogant. But, as I say, I was a little bit of a rebel and if they was arrogant with me I could be arrogant with them very quickly. I wouldn't just sit down to that attitude. And - but on the whole as I say, with them - m
o
st of us were in the same position, most women and there was no work for women of course, there wasn't work for men. And - even if a woman had a career she - when she got married she had to give it up because - the question of depression. But, as I said, 
my children never went hungry, they never had luxuries. One couldn't afford it. But they always had a - a substantial meal, one meal - one substantial meal a day, even if it was only a stew you know, they had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When your husband was home did he have a lot to do with the children and did he help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. And - whilst he was at work I didn't expect my husband to come home and do the housework. And he would help me after tea, he would help me wash the children and that - u
ndress the children and wash them and get them to bed. So that we did have our evenings on our own. And he wouldn't allow, he didn't want the children - neither did I, I felt well I'd had 'em all day long and they'd been up early and they could go to bed 
early. It was good for them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What time did they go to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well I - the youngest one, whoever was the youngest, was bathed and - and fed and put to bed by six o'clock and then the ages ranged up but they were all in bed before eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you know what your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, I always knew, he never kept it from me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you discuss how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes, he used to talk about - well he used to leave it to me and I used to say well, I'd got to get so a
nd so, and if he - if he did have a shilling to spare I could have it, we never argued over money. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you do all the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What about making clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I wasn't too good at tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 t }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 -but I used to, I used to make enough for the children you know, to please - to please myself, I couldn't have made it to have pleased other people. I used to - I'd cut down - I'd buy a pair of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 pyjama}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  jackets at a sale and cut them down and make little petticoats and knickers for the kids. And that sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you grow any vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No, we never had a garden, we were in rooms and then we were in a flat for years. But when we - we moved into a house in 1938 and we did grow a few vegetables. In fact during the war we grew vegetables at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were the children allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 Oh no. Well not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
 exactly - I - I didn't stop them from talking but I used to say to them - to them, stop talking and get on with your eating, you know, sort of bus
iness but - oh yes, I made them behave themselves at the table. But my father had been so strict with me at the table and with us that - well, as I say, I - I - I used to say to them, well - oh stop the talking and get on with the eating and I would make 
t
hem - behave themselves at the table and - teach them table manners. But I was a little bit more relaxed than when my father was live because father was so strict at the table that our lives were a misery - they were really a misery at the table. We wasn'
t
 allowed to look up, speak, breathe or anything else. And - if you wanted - you couldn't leave the table until you'd said grace and you had to ask, well I made my children to that. They always said their grace and asked if they could leave the table befor
e they left.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When your children were young did you feel there was a right way and a wrong way to bring up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well, yes, I - I thought that they - they should - respect and mind their elders. They had to do as they were told. I never said,
 well - will you go and do so and so for me, if they came in and I wanted an errand I used to say to them, will you go up to the shop please and get so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your husband have similar sort of ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. He was the same, he wasn't - I h
ad a - more patience with the children than he - you know, of course, I suppose it was really that - he'd had a lot of illness and he possibly couldn't stand them quite so much. I could get on the floor and play with them and all this sort of business.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You told me that you didn't think you were an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not really, not to show affection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You weren't demonstrative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No. No. I still am not. This is something I've never been able to do, my sister can and I've got a daughter 
that can, but I can't. I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 But you felt that affection was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you want your children to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. And they always have, even to day I mean, if they've got any worries they come round to mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you let them join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No, I'm afraid I didn't, I was brought up with that rigid idea children should be seen and not heard and I - I used to say to them, if there was anybody there, now 
I'm talking. You wait for a minute and then tell me what you want. It's the same with John if he come in, I say, now John, nanny's talking and - you'll have to come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When you were ill or having a baby who helped you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 I always had a woman i
n to look after me, we did that you know, engaged a woman to come in for fourteen days, and my husband was very very good when I was having my children, and the bigger children well they were taught they had to wash up and that sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So you managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes. In some cases, but - I was a little bit on the independent side, I could get everything done before I had my babies, even to the last day I would wash if there was any dirty clothes about so that they w
ouldn't be left for the - woman to have to do when she came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were there any other children you discouraged your children from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not really. If a child - if I found out a child was swearing a great deal then I used to say to them, 
well you - because that child swears you mustn't swear, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 If they did something you disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well they would be punished if it was very very serious, they would be punished, but otherwise I used to just tell them off 
and tell they they oughtn't to do it again and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Who would punish them, would it be you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh me, not their father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What sort of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - just give 'em a smack, you know. Not too drastic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Would you say that your 
children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both parents or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh I think they did from both of us. But I think in most cases if a mother can - can do this sort of thing they do
 take more from the mother because the mother's with them more isn't she, it's - I mean, one's got to face this fact because if a father doesn't get home 'til six o'clock at night, he comes home and he's been working hard he gets tired as well as mother a
nd he tends to relax. And of course my children used to go to bed so that father didn't have a great deal to do with them, not in the evening time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Can you think of anything you did in the home, you say you used to play games and romp with the childre
n, if they had a birthday did anything happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, I used to - even though I never had a great deal of money I would make up a little cake for them and stick a couple of candles on it and - if there was a couple of little kiddies lived nearby and th
ey wanted them in and - and they used to play games between them, last for about hour or two hours and - that was as far as one could go in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh Christmas, we always made a great deal of Christmas, Christmas was the kids
' day and we treated it as such. And right up until last Christmas my family all came home. I'd have forty-three of them here for Christmas morning. And the grandchildren, great-grandchildren, the whole family. And this happened every Christmas. Christmas
 
tree up in that corner, parcels all round, presents and they were always given out on a Christmas night. And even in our sort of - hard up days as I call it we always made something for Christmas for the children. This has continued right the way through.
 
And of course this Christmas my husband only died two days before the Christmas so that everything - well we - we didn't make the children miserable, we had our lunch here and - we went down to my daughter's on the night time - the teenagers and that went
 
down to the other daughter's who lives nearby and they had their radiogram on with their records and we let them enjoy themselves, their grandfather wouldn't have wished them to have been miserable, and he wouldn't. And we just sat round, you know, talkin
g and - having a - trying to make the best of it. Yes. It wasn't - he - he wouldn't have wished for someone to have made it - anybody else miserable, mind you I felt miserable naturally didn't I, but - the children had their Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And Christmas has always been a traditional family time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well it is, yes. Yes, it is. And I suppose it will be this Christmas again, we won't - we won't drop it because of that, as a matter of fact there's a big box upstairs with all Christmas presents in still that
 were never given out. So that - so we get them this Christmas. The children had theirs, the children did have theirs. And of course we didn't have the Christmas tree up. Every day I kept saying to my daughter, we'll have to get that Christmas tree up, th
e
 Christmas tree didn't go up, so we - we didn't, no. But - oh yes, Christmas - I've got some photographs somewhere, I don't know where they are offhand, and see you know the Christmas tree with all the presents round it sort of thing. Yes. My two sisters 
and their husbands come down and then all my own children and their husbands and wives and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you used to take your children out visiting neighbours, friends or relatives?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not a great deal, I would tea them occasionally because I always felt 
kiddies, if you took them into someone else's house and they'd got a nice little home and - kids started interfering and - and I - I guaranteed - it didn't matter how well behaved your child was if you took then out they'd misbehave so - I never found - I
 used to say I never had any angels, mine never sprouted wings. And - I - I - another thing I didn't have a great deal of time to go visiting people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your husband ever take them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - he would take them out for a walk on a Sunday morning perhaps you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well we used to go from the church, they had a camp and we used to go there which was very cheap and - we went there, that was our holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 With your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 With the children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How did you spend Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Mostly like every other day really. Saturday was given to going out shopping and that sort of thing. And we always used to buy some comics up the rod, they used to sell them cheaply and we'd buy them and 
- -buy some sweets and give them for Sunday morning, that's a regular thing for them for their comics and sweets on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes, I used to belong to the library.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you read aloud to each other or the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Used to read to the children, you know, the smaller ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did the children go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. My children all went to church, yes. They were all confirmed in the; Church of England - all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you think it wrong that they would work or enjoy themselves on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No, I never had that attitude. It was very - very very rife when I was a child, you wasn't allowed to breathe and if you went out on a Sunday well you went to church and you went for a walk and you ca
me home, you wasn't allowed to do anything and this was most boring for the child. So that I relaxed this with my own children I didn't let them go mad of course, but they went to Sunday school. And - they went to church of a morning and they went in the 
a
fternoon - the bigger ones sometimes went evenings too. But, if one Sunday they would say, I don't want to go to Sunday school today, I didn't make them go, but what I used to say to them, well all right, you can stop at home this week but you'll go next 
w
eek. And I found that they went. You see, they - I - I - and I think if I'd have made them go they would have possibly played truant. So - I - I didn't, I - I took my own childhood back you see, I - I thought to myself, well I used to detest having to do 
these things on a Sunday. Yes, I thought about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did they have to put on different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well if you had them, if you had these things for them they did but - I think most people tended to put the children on something different on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh gosh, yes, for years. From 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 That's when you could first vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 No, I couldn't vote them. I wasn't allowed to vote 'til I was thirty. When we first got the vote they had to be thirty and t
hen they reduced it to twenty-one didn't they. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So why did you start taking an interest in politics then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well - from the days of childhood my father used to talk about politics and trade unions and I think that sort of - I grew up with it. 
Then after the war my husband joined the Labour party and I went with him and joined. I - couldn't take a very active part because of the children but - now and again he would - I would go to a woman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 s meeting and he would look after - you know, look after
 the children while I went, that was why I became interested. And then of course gradually as I got older I joined the Co-operative Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 s Guild and - of course used to take part in quite a lot of politics - it was on the political side a bit. Yes. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 How has your interest developed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, well I - I suppose it developed by going to meetings, by the way people had to live, by the conditions they lived under. The hard times that we had to experience we had something to fight for, something to work for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You've worked for the Labour party ever since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When did you first become interested in the council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh - I would say nearly forty years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Any special reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well, because I used to go to, you see, the Labour party meetings where you got reports from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 councillors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
 and that sort of thing and it made me take an interest in how - how the local authority was run, how rates were formed and everything else up to that time such as went on in my own sweet way and I wasn't interested in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 councillors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
 or the Mayor or anybody else. And then a - by virtue of the fact that I went to the Labour party meetings I realised that these people were doing a job and a jobly good job and started taking an interest
 in how they - the council was run and how it worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When were you first elected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 In 1945.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Was your husband equally interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. More so really because he did quite a lot of the running of it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes, he was Secretary of our Ward Association. I became Chairman - Vice Chairman of our association and then my husband went as - elected as a delegate to the central party which was the - the - main - part of the movement because it controlled all t
he other parts, and he eventually became Secretary of the Central Labour party, well that is - disbanded in 1965 when we came under the greater London Council. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 What year were you Mayor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 1966 - '67.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Were you more active in politics and local government - than your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Oh no, he was equally as active because he used to be what we called a - a representative on the group of - of the Labour party, that was the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 councillors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  meeting they - they had. He was their representative
, of course he wasn't allowed to take part in any of the council business, but he was interested a great deal. He couldn't sit for the council because he was a council employee. They're not allowed to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And this is how you became involved?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You've got so many interests now haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes. Well I did have then, and when I was first - was first elected to the council in '45 I went in - onto the Goodmayes Mental Hospital Committee and the South Upton Mentally Defective 
Committee and of course there was a couple of sub-committees on that. I was on the old West Ham Electricity Committee which because we had our own power station, and the Old Age Pensions Committee, and - on the Miners. Well then I gave up one committee an
d
 went on housing. Well then when nationalization came in force in '48 Goodmayes went under the Hospital Management and Ockenden and of course our Electricity Committee - our electricity became nationalized. So I went onto Finance Committee and Health Comm
i
ttee then, and Housing Committee I was on for a number of years. And - then I came off of the housing and finance and went on to Higher Age and the works Committee, and of course there were several sub-committees attached to that, there was - I went on th
e
 libraries again, I was on Libraries Committee there times I think altogether - and then under the Workers Committee there was the - Fire Brigade, I was on that, and the Highways, there was the Horticultural and Street Trading, I was on both of those and 
I
 had the Health Committee of course there was two or three sub-committees attached to that. And of course I was elected onto the Clean Air Council and the Home Counties. I'm still on that - I'm still on - and I'm a representative to the - National Institu
t
e of the Blind and from the council. And for the Southern Region Association of the Blind and the Deaf. I'm on both of those. One times I was on the Unmarried Council, that's the - the Council of the Unmarried mother and her child. And I was on the Marria
ge Guidance Council, but I don't go on those know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 During all this time have your views changed very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
No, not at all. I don't think they ever will, you know, I - I - how can I put this, this is rather difficult, I still feel that there's lot
s of thing that the working man can have done for him. There's all this question about dockers earning all this money and all that money but they don't earn all that money as it said in the paper. They can do overtime and make their money up. And this I a
m against, I say that if a man is given a real working and living wage he doesn't e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 ar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
ned to do overtime, he's given shorter hours for leisure and he shouldn't have to work over time. I do feel in some cases that some of the working men could pull their weig
ht a little bit more, I'm quite honest about this. And I believe in a man or a woman getting a fair wage for a fair days work. And if they got a fair wage fore a fair days work they wouldn't have to do overtime or want to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 So things in fact haven't changed a great deal in that respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Not at all. No, they haven't - they haven't. The only point that - that has changed is because there is more employment about and people are not unemployed. And this is the most terribly - terrible thing of t
he lot. And of course again when people are unemployed to day they do get help. But when they were unemployed when I was a child they didn't get any help. And as I say, and I often say this, we saw more days than we saw dinners, when I was young. But that
 
isn't so today. They still say I know that there's still - people who don't earn a big wage and the children need more money and that sort of thing, I believe this is true, but I do feel that we as youngsters were taught how to cook a meal and to make - t
o
 get the best out of a meal and unfortunately I don't think that's the case today with a lot of people. Now, I - I saw on the wireless one night - on the television rather, they were giving the - an account of the under developed children, and this was a;
 case of a man and a wife and I think about seven children living in a terrible - appalling place, ou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 gh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
t to be - ought to have been pulled down, the man was unemployed, they were in receipt of Social Security and the woman said that they - she could only af
ford sausages. Well my - to my mind sausages are the dearest thing you can buy to get a meal out of. I mean you've got to pay at least three and sixpence for a pound of sausages, and what's in a pound of sausage believe me I don't know, I - I think they'r
e
 a luxury. I know you - you've got pay quite a good price for a pound of meat, but if that woman had gone and got some - gone and got some bones and have let them stew for a good few hours and put plenty of cereals in them like what we call soup mixture a
nd peas and haricot beans and lentils and that sort of thing and plenty of vegetables in and made a dumpling she'd have given her children far more nour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 shment than frying them a pan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 ful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12666972\charrsid16671506 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506  of sausages. And you see this is the way we were brought up. And this is - I'm afraid - unfortunately the people don't understand today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 In your day you were taught to use what you'd got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 We were taught - what we'd got and make the best use of it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 When you were first married do you think then that some people felt under pressure to vote the same as their employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Oh yes. Oh yes, still in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Well - of course he didn't vote until he was twenty-one, until he come out of the army but he voted Labour, his fath
er was a strict trade unionist and if you were a member of trade unions they - it was impressed into their children that they must vote for Labour you see, this was it. But you see I'm quite - I don't know whether it was unfortunate or not, I think it's u
n
fortunate that today the youngsters have had a - in most cases have had the opportunity of having a good education and - they get on in the world and this I - I apploaud, I mean, if you don't give a kid an education you expect them to stop where they are,
 
but I do feel that having done that they get snobbish and they don't want to vote for the working class, or they don't want to vote Labour. They think the Labour people are against them but they forget that it was Labour people what put them where they ar
e
. You see, and this is the trouble today. I mean, we found this out the last general election. See? And again you see there are some people that never tell their children the hard times they had, and there are children that don't want to know, they say, o
h
 that's years ago, it couldn't happen today. But it could - it could. I mean if unemployment rife it could go back to the old days, because if people are not working they can't pay the taxes. I do feel that - there are some employers - I mean there are hu
m
ane employers, like who try to give as much as they can to their people, but there's still the employers that still want to make the profits. You see, there's so much shareholding business today in firms and the shareholders who do nothing towards making 
that - factory or whatever the - their - or the goods, still want their profits from it. I might be sounding a little bit on the Leftist when I talk like that but - it isn't that. I - I feel that - that the - the workers would share in the profits.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 And you're speaking from experience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Yes. Yes. You see, the idea of the - the - the old Socialist conception was that the worker should secure - the profit - for - for his work and his brain, and this is true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 You've grown up with politics around you all the time, in your early married life did you have other leisure activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Well I used to go round - we used to have a social club round the church, we used to go round there and we used to have - ran a little social you know, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you ever go to music halls or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 
Occasionally, I never had much time to go to music halls or pictures, I didn't get much time - and money I mean, let's fact it, if it was a shilling - sixpence at the pictures well it was sixpence you probably wanted indoors and you just couldn't do it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308090 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Did you have many friends you and your husband, did people drop in to see you or did you go to visit people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4462485 AG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7304844\charrsid16671506 Not a great many, we had certain friends that used to come and see us and cer
tain friends we used to go and see but of course I didn't do very much, I say, with a family you can't do a lot of visiting I mean, it's just impossible. I used to go up to my sister that was younger than I, I used to go up to her place and they used to c
ome down to us. And my sister was musical but she could play a piano and we all used to sort of enjoy ourselves in our own way.
